<subSubSection lastPageId="47" lastPageNumber="48" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="44.[189,334,1262,1288]" box="[189,334,1262,1288]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,334,1262,1288]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,334,1262,1288]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="44.[189,506,1309,1371]" box="[234,325,1309,1335]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[234,325,1309,1335]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Female</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="44.[189,506,1309,1371]" box="[189,506,1344,1371]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
BODY LENGTH. 5.0– 
<quantity box="[409,501,1344,1371]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.6" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" unit="mm" value="5.6">5.6 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="44.[189,1399,1409,1576]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
HEAD. Head wider than long. Integument black, except part of mandibles dark reddish-brown. Face sparsely covered with long, greyish, erect hair (
<figureCitation box="[766,879,1444,1471]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="45.[189,232,1964,1990]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,591,1922]" captionTargetId="figure@45.[189,1399,590,1923]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="Fig. 23. Scrapter punctatus sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Head (SEM). C. Thorax (dorsal view). D. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). E. Metasoma (dorsal view). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860642" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860642/files/figure.png" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Fig. 23A</figureCitation>
). Clypeus strongly convex with coarse and dense punctation (i = 1–2 d); surface between punctures apically smooth and shiny, basally superficially shagreened but shiny (
<figureCitation box="[452,560,1515,1541]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="45.[189,232,1964,1990]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,591,1922]" captionTargetId="figure@45.[189,1399,590,1923]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="Fig. 23. Scrapter punctatus sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Head (SEM). C. Thorax (dorsal view). D. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). E. Metasoma (dorsal view). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860642" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860642/files/figure.png" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Fig. 23B</figureCitation>
). Malar area medially narrow, almost linear. Antenna dorsally blackishbrown, ventrally yellowish-brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="44.[189,1399,1615,1783]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
MESOSOMA. Integument black. Mesoscutal disc between punctures superficially reticulate, shiny; disc densely (i = 1–2 d) and coarsely punctate (
<figureCitation box="[716,805,1651,1677]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="45.[189,232,1964,1990]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,591,1922]" captionTargetId="figure@45.[189,1399,590,1923]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="Fig. 23. Scrapter punctatus sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Head (SEM). C. Thorax (dorsal view). D. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). E. Metasoma (dorsal view). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860642" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860642/files/figure.png" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
C–D). Metanotum about as long as basal area of propodeum, apically with narrow, indistinct carinate depression (
<figureCitation box="[932,1039,1686,1712]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="45.[189,232,1964,1990]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,591,1922]" captionTargetId="figure@45.[189,1399,590,1923]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="Fig. 23. Scrapter punctatus sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Head (SEM). C. Thorax (dorsal view). D. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). E. Metasoma (dorsal view). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860642" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860642/files/figure.png" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Fig. 23D</figureCitation>
). Propodeum basally shallowly but broadly carinate (
<figureCitation box="[446,557,1721,1747]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="45.[189,232,1964,1990]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,591,1922]" captionTargetId="figure@45.[189,1399,590,1923]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="Fig. 23. Scrapter punctatus sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Head (SEM). C. Thorax (dorsal view). D. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). E. Metasoma (dorsal view). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860642" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860642/files/figure.png" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Fig. 23D</figureCitation>
). Mesoscutum, scutellum, metanotum, mesepisternum and propodeum sparsely covered with short, greyish, erect hair (
<figureCitation box="[752,862,1756,1782]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="45.[189,232,1964,1990]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,591,1922]" captionTargetId="figure@45.[189,1399,590,1923]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="Fig. 23. Scrapter punctatus sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Head (SEM). C. Thorax (dorsal view). D. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). E. Metasoma (dorsal view). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860642" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860642/files/figure.png" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Fig. 23A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="44.[189,1110,1822,1848]" box="[189,1110,1822,1848]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">WINGS. Slightly yellowish-brown; wing venation and stigma yellowish-brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="44.[189,1398,1887,1949]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">LEGS. Integument black to dark reddish-brown; fore and mid tibia basally sometimes with small yellowish spot. Vestiture greyish-white, scopa greyish-white, dorsally blackish-brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="45.[189,1399,267,540]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
METASOMA. Integument black, apical margins of terga broadly translucent yellowish to reddish-brown (
<figureCitation box="[198,303,302,329]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="45.[189,232,1964,1990]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,591,1922]" captionTargetId="figure@45.[189,1399,590,1923]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="Fig. 23. Scrapter punctatus sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Head (SEM). C. Thorax (dorsal view). D. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). E. Metasoma (dorsal view). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860642" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860642/files/figure.png" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Fig. 23E</figureCitation>
). Discs of T1 and T2 without hair; following terga with sparse and very short but increasingly more and longer hair; T2 (and sometimes T3) basally with a medially very narrow, laterally much broader band of very fine, short and erect silverish hair; apical tergal hair bands missing on all terga (
<figureCitation box="[198,307,408,434]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="45.[189,232,1964,1990]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,591,1922]" captionTargetId="figure@45.[189,1399,590,1923]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="Fig. 23. Scrapter punctatus sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Head (SEM). C. Thorax (dorsal view). D. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). E. Metasoma (dorsal view). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860642" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860642/files/figure.png" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Fig. 23E</figureCitation>
). Prepygidial and pygidial fimbriae greyish-brown. T1 densely (i = 0.5–1 d) and finely to indistinctly punctate, between punctures polished to superficially sculptured and shiny; T2–T4 smoorh or superficially sculptured, shiny, with dense, fine, indistinct to fine punctation; T2–T4 with polished or superficially sculptured, broad and shiny apical tergal depression (
<figureCitation box="[965,1072,514,540]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="45.[189,232,1964,1990]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,591,1922]" captionTargetId="figure@45.[189,1399,590,1923]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="Fig. 23. Scrapter punctatus sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Head (SEM). C. Thorax (dorsal view). D. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). E. Metasoma (dorsal view). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860642" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860642/files/figure.png" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Fig. 23E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
